         <abstract>
            <p>This note presents nearly-best rational approximations for the Coulomb phase shift &lt;tex-math&gt;$\sigma_0(\eta) = \arg \Gamma(1+ i_\eta)$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. Maximal relative errors range down to between 4.24 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-19&lt;/sup&gt; and 1.09 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-20&lt;/sup&gt;. The nontrivial zero of σ&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt;(η) is also given.</p>
          </abstract>
